		h3 Rows & Columns

		p To create a grid, use the .row class (clears the floats), then .column-{number} classes for different column widths.
		p Columns work in the following way:



		.example
			.columns
				.columns-4 Columns 4
				.columns-5 Columns 5
				.columns-3 Columns 3

		pre
			code.language-html
				| &lt;div class="columns"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-4"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-5"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-3"&gt;
				| &lt;/div&gt;


		p Helper classes are also available to create different grids for different breakpoints.

		.example

			.columns
				.columns-4-device-small.columns-5-device-medium Columns 4
				.columns-4-device-small.columns-3-device-medium  Columns 5
				.columns-4-device-small.columns-4-device-medium  Columns 3

		pre
			code.language-html
				| &lt;div class="columns"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-4-device-small"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-5-device-small"&gt;
				|  &lt;div class="columns-3-device-small"&gt;
				| &lt;/div&gt;


		h3 Offsets

		.example
			.columns
				.columns-4.offset-8 Columns 4
